{{italic title}}
'''''Brodsko kolo''''' ({{lang-en|The [[kolo (dance)]] of Brod}}) is an annual festival of [[folklore]] held in [[Slavonski Brod]], [[Croatia]]. The festival was founded in 1962, and is considered one of the major cultural events of the whole of [[Slavonia]], together with ''[[Vinkovačke jeseni]]'' and ''[[Đakovački vezovi]]''. Until 1991 it was referred to under the generic name "Smotra folklora" (Folklore festival).<ref>{{cite journal | url = http://hrcak.srce.hr/index.php?show=clanak&id_clanak_jezik=112509 | journal = Studia ethnologica Croatica | volume = 4 | number = 1 |date=March 1993 | publisher = Department of Ethnology and Cultural Anthropology, [[Faculty of Humanities and Social Sciences, University of Zagreb]] | issn = 1330-3627 | title = Baranja je "tvrd orah". Analiza istraživanja i popularizacije tradicijske baranjske folklorne glazbe |trans-title=Baranja is "tough nut". Records and popularisation analysis of traditional Baranja folk music | first = Miroslava | last = Hadžihusejnović-Valašek | language = Croatian | page = 194 | format = PDF | accessdate = 2012-02-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.brodsko-kolo.com/Povijest.html | title = Povijest Brodskog kola | language = Croatian | publisher = Folklorni ansambl Broda/Folklore Ensemble of Brod | date = 2009-02-20 | accessdate = 2012-02-12 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080607083622/http://www.brodsko-kolo.com/Povijest.html | archivedate = 2008-06-07 | df =  }}</ref>

