In the religion of [[Haitian Vodou]], '''Captain Debas''' (also '''Debard''', '''Deebat''') is a [[loa]] of the [[ghede]].

According to "Secrets of voodoo"{{clarify|date=April 2014}} Captain Debas is part of the [[Rada loa|rada]] nation, not ghede, and should be served in rada rites rather than ghede rite.  Is a family loa and can be combined with any other loa of any nation who allows families. Originates from [[Africa]] and is originally from [[Vodoun]].

