{{Infobox religious building |image = MassawaMosque.jpg |caption = |building_name = Mosque of the Companions |native_name = ''Masjid aṣ-Ṣaḥābah'' ({{lang-ar|مَـسْـجِـد الـصَّـحَـابَـة}}) |location = [[Massawa]], [[Eritrea]] |geo = {{coord|15.611240|39.481153|display=inline}} |religious_affiliation = [[Islam]] |region = [[Northeast Africa]] |province = |website = |architect = |architecture_type = [[Mosque]] |architecture_style = |year_completed = 620's or 630's<ref name="Reid2012Massawa"/> |construction_cost = |capacity = |dome_quantity = |dome_height_outer = |dome_dia_outer = |minaret_quantity = |minaret_height = }}
The '''Mosque of the Companions''' ({{lang-ar|مَـسْـجِـد الـصَّـحَـابَـة|Masjid aṣ-Ṣaḥābah}}) is a [[mosque]] in the city of [[Massawa]], [[Eritrea]]. Dating to the early [[7th century]] [[Common Era|CE]], it is believed to be the [[List of the oldest mosques#Africa|first mosque]] on the [[Africa]]n continent.<ref name="HistoireIslamique2014">{{cite news |url=https://histoireislamique.wordpress.com/2014/06/15/listedes-premieres-mosquees-au-monde/ |title=Liste des premières mosquées au monde prophètique, rashidun et omeyyade selon les écris historique et les traces archéologiques |date=2014-06-15 |work=Histoire Islamique |access-date=2017-09-24 |language=fr-FR}}</ref> It was reportedly built by [[Sahaba|companions]] of the [[Prophets and messengers in Islam|Islamic ''Nabī'']] ({{lang-ar|نَـبِي}}, [[Prophet]]) [[Muhammad]] who came [[Northeast Africa|here]] to flee [[persecution of Muslims by the Meccans|persecution by people]] in the [[Hejaz]]i<ref name="MWGD2001">{{cite book |last= |first= |coauthors= |title=Merriam-Webster's Geographical Dictionary |page=479 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Co_VIPIJerIC&pg=PA479 |year=2001 |isbn=0 87779 546 0 |access-date=2013-03-17}}</ref> city of [[Mecca]], present-day [[Saudi Arabia]].<ref name="Reid2012Massawa">{{cite book |last=Reid |first=Richard J. |title=A History of Modern Africa: 1800 to the Present |publisher=[[John Wiley and Sons]] |chapter=The Islamic Frontier in Eastern Africa |page=106 |isbn=0470658983 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=US6RQtYwasUC&pg |date=12 January 2012 |access-date=15 March 2015}}</ref>
