'''Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership''' ('''RCEP''') is a proposed [[Free Trade Agreement|free trade agreement]] (FTA) between the ten member states of the [[Association of Southeast Asian Nations]] (ASEAN) ([[Brunei]], [[Cambodia]], [[Indonesia]], [[Laos]], [[Malaysia]], [[Myanmar]], the [[Philippines]], [[Singapore]], [[Thailand]], [[Vietnam]]) and the six Asia-Pacific states with which ASEAN has existing free trade agreements ([[Australia]], [[China]], [[India]], [[Japan]], [[South Korea]] and [[New Zealand]]). It is reported that a broad agreement is likely to be reached in November 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/2162395/japans-relations-china-back-normal-track-says-shinzo-abe|title=US trade war and Japan push raise prospects for China-backed Asia free-trade deal|author=South China Morning Post|date=Sep 3, 2018|website=}}</ref>

RCEP negotiations were formally launched in November 2012 at the ASEAN Summit in Cambodia.<ref name=Challenges>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsis.edu.sg/publications/Perspective/RSIS1402013.pdf|title=RCEP: Challenges and Opportunities for India, 25 July 2013, RSIS, Singapore|author=|date=|website=rsis.edu.sg|access-date=24 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131230233448/http://www.rsis.edu.sg/publications/Perspective/RSIS1402013.pdf#|archive-date=30 December 2013|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The free trade agreement is scheduled and expected to be signed in November 2018 during the ASEAN Summit and Related Summit in Singapore, after the first RCEP summit was held on 14 November 2017 in [[Manila]], Philippines.<ref>{{cite news|title=RCEP likely to be signed in November 2018: PM|url=http://www.thesundaily.my/news/2017/11/15/rcep-likely-be-signed-november-2018-pm|work=www.thesundaily.my|language=en}}</ref> RCEP is viewed as an alternative to the [[Trans-Pacific Partnership]] (TPP), a proposed trade agreement which includes several Asian and American nations but excludes China and India.<ref name=TPP>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2015/10/14/tpp-deal-pressures-rcep-trade-talks-in-busan-china-keen-for-progress.html|title=RCEP: The next trade deal you need to know about|first=See Kit|last=Tang|date=14 October 2015|website=cnbc.com}}</ref>

In 2017, prospective RCEP member states accounted for a population of 3.4 billion people with a total [[Gross Domestic Product]] (GDP, PPP) of $49.5 trillion, approximately 39 percent of the world's GDP,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2016/12/07/rcep-talks-speed-up-amid-tpp-failure.html |title=RCEP talks speed up amid TPP failure |author=Stefani Ribka/Linda Yulisman |date=December 7, 2016}}</ref> with the combined GDPs of China and India making up more than half that amount.

RCEP is the world's largest [[Trade bloc|economic bloc]], covering nearly half of the global economy.<ref name="auto">{{cite news|title=Najib: RCEP likely to be signed in Nov 2018|url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/malaysia/article/najib-rcep-likely-to-be-signed-in-nov-2018#kLhIUr0450ITuVJx.97|date=15 November 2017}}</ref> [[List of countries by past and projected GDP (PPP)#Long term GDP estimates|According to estimates by PwC]], the [[Gross Domestic Product]] (GDP, PPP) of RCEP member states is likely to amount to nearly $250 trillion by 2050, or a quarter of a [[quadrillion]] dollars, with the combined GDPs of China and India making up more than 75% of the amount. RCEP's share of the global economy could account for half of the estimated $0.5 quadrillion global GDP (PPP) by 2050.

==Membership==
[[File:RCEP.png|thumb|500px|right|The 16 member countries of the RCEP <br> <span style="color:#1743a6">'''Blue'''</span>: [[ASEAN]] <br> <span style="color:#6330d5">'''Purple'''</span>: [[ASEAN#ASEAN Plus Three|ASEAN Plus Three]] <br> <span style="color:#0d63ac">'''Teal'''</span>: [[ASEAN#ASEAN Plus Six|ASEAN Plus Six]]]]

The arrangement is also open to any other external economic partners, such as nations in Central Asia and remaining nations in South Asia and Oceania.<ref name="What is">[http://www.fta.gov.sg/press_release%5CFACTSHEET%20ON%20RCEP_final.pdf What is the Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP)? Ministry of Trade and Industry Singapore November 2012]{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

