==Presence in the world==
[[File:RCEP Population.png|thumb|250px|right|RCEP Population - 2012 : IMF - World Economic Outlook Databases (October 2013)]]
[[File:RCEP GDP.png|thumb|250px|right|RCEP GDP - 2012 :  IMF - World Economic Outlook Databases (October 2013)]]
RCEP potentially includes more than 3 billion people or 45% of the world's population, and a combined GDP of about $21.3 trillion, accounting for about 40 percent of world trade.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thediplomat.com/pacific-money/2013/07/30/regional-comprehensive-economic-partnership-rcep-issues-and-way-forward/|title=Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP): Issues and Way Forward|first=Rohit Sinha and Geethanjali Nataraj, The|last=Diplomat|date=|website=thediplomat.com}}</ref> The combined GDP of potential RCEP members surpassed the combined GDP of [[Trans-Pacific Partnership]] (TPP) members in 2007. Continued growth, particularly in [[China]], [[India]] and [[Indonesia]] could see total GDP in RCEP grow to over $100 trillion by 2050, roughly double the project size of TPP economies.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.eaber.org/node/25601|title=Understanding and applying long-term GDP projections {{!}} EABER|website=www.eaber.org|access-date=2016-06-17}}</ref>

[[File:GDP projection for RCEP countries to 2050.png|thumb|GDP projections for potential RCEP member countries to 2050.<ref name=":0" />]]
On January 23, 2017, United States President [[Donald Trump]] signed a memorandum that stated withdrawal of the country from the TPP, a move which is seen to improve the chances of success for RCEP.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zdnet.com/article/trump-dumping-trans-pacific-partnership/|title=Trump dumping Trans-Pacific Partnership - ZDNet|first=Corinne|last=Reichert|date=|website=zdnet.com}}</ref>

==History and timeline==
* During the 19th ASEAN Summit held 14–19 November 2011, the Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP) was introduced.<ref>[http://www.asean.org/news/item/asean-structure-asean-summit Nineteenth ASEAN Summit, Bali, Indonesia | 14-19 November 2011] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130629110759/http://www.asean.org/news/item/asean-structure-asean-summit |date=29 June 2013 }}</ref>
* The 44th ASEAN Economic Ministers (AEM) Meeting and Related Meetings were held in Siem Reap, Cambodia, 25 August - 1 September 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.cntv.cn/program/newsupdate/20120901/101251.shtml|title=ASEAN plus 6 agree to start RCEP talks  CCTV News - CNTV English|author=|date=|website=english.cntv.cn}}</ref>
* Leaders at the 21st ASEAN Summit held 18–20 November 2012 in Phnom Penh, Cambodia endorsed the framework of RCEP and announced the launch of their negotiations.<ref name=Announcement>[http://www.meti.go.jp/english/press/2012/1120_02.html Announcement of the Launch of Negotiations for the Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP)  Ministry of Economy, Trade and Industry Japan 20 November 2012] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014130209/http://www.meti.go.jp/english/press/2012/1120_02.html |date=14 October 2013 }}</ref>
*The 1st round of RCEP negotiation was held on May 9–13, 2013 in Brunei<ref name="Joint Statement">{{cite web|url=http://www.asean.org/news/asean-statement-communiques/item/regional-comprehensive-economic-partnership-rcep-joint-statement-the-first-meeting-of-trade-negotiating-committee|title= Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP) Joint Statement The First Meeting of Trade Negotiating Committee|darte=10 May 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150219224756/http://www.asean.org/news/asean-statement-communiques/item/regional-comprehensive-economic-partnership-rcep-joint-statement-the-first-meeting-of-trade-negotiating-committee%7Carchivedate%3DFebruary 19, 2015</ref>
* The 2nd round of RCEP negotiation was held on September 23–27, 2013 in Brisbane, Australia.<ref>[http://www.dfat.gov.au/media/releases/department/2013/dfat-release-20131003.html Australia hosts second round of Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP) Negotiations in Brisbane] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131003141637/http://www.dfat.gov.au/media/releases/department/2013/dfat-release-20131003.html |date=3 October 2013 }}</ref>
* The 3rd round of RCEP negotiation was held on  January 20–24, 2014 in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.<ref>[http://www.miti.gov.my/cms/content.jsp?id=com.tms.cms.article.Article_d1241f52-c0a8156f-72974691-4887df24 Media Release : 3rd Meeting of the RCEP Trade Negotiation Committee 20-24 January 2014, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia | 27 Jan 2014 08:40 AM | The Ministry of International Trade and Industry, Malaysia] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222040611/http://www.miti.gov.my/cms/content.jsp?id=com.tms.cms.article.Article_d1241f52-c0a8156f-72974691-4887df24 |date=22 February 2014 }}</ref>
*The 4th round of RCEP negotiation was held on 31 March – 4 April 2014 in [[Nanning, China]] .<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.meti.go.jp/english/press/2014/0404_01.html|title=Fourth Round of Negotiations for Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP)|publisher=Joint press release of Japanese Ministry of Economy, Trade, and Industry with the Ministry of Foreign Affairs|date=2014-04-04}}</ref>
*The 5th round of RCEP negotiation was held on June 21–27, 2014 in Singapore.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.moit.gov.vn/en/News/628/5th-negotiation-of-regional-comprehensive-economic-partnership-agreement-%28rcep%29.aspx | title=5th negotiation of Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership Agreement (RCEP) | publisher=Ministry of Industry and Trade of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam | date=30 June 2014 | accessdate=20 December 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222104412/http://www.moit.gov.vn/en/News/628/5th-negotiation-of-regional-comprehensive-economic-partnership-agreement-%28rcep%29.aspx# | archive-date=22 December 2015 | dead-url=yes | df=dmy-all }}</ref>
*The 6th round of RCEP negotiation and related meetings was held on December 1–5, 2014 in New Delhi, India.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://commerce.nic.in/MOC/press_release.asp?id=3134|title=Department of commerce|author=|date=|website=commerce.nic.in}}</ref> The Indians held an outreach event with their business community to educate them on the goals of RCEP. The Japanese asked to set up a workshop on e-Commerce.
*The 7th round of RCEP negotiation was held on February 9–13, 2015 in Bangkok, Thailand. An expert group on electronic commerce met during this round. The Asian Trade Centre (based in Singapore) submitted a proposal regarding an e-Commerce chapter and gave a presentation on the paper.
*The 8th round of RCEP negotiation was held on June  5–13, 2015 in Kyoto, Japan.
*The 9th round of RCEP negotiation was held on August 3–7, 2015 in Nay Pyi Taw, Myanmar.
*The 10th round of RCEP negotiation was held on October 12–16, 2015 in Busan, South Korea in . The meetings took place at BEXCO (Busan's Convention and Exhibition Centre). This round included the first region wide stakeholder meeting (organized by the Singapore-based Asian Trade Centre) which involved an informal meeting between government officials and business representatives over lunch followed by an afternoon seminar focused on what RCEP can do to help business operate in the e-Commerce space.
*The 11th round of RCEP negotiation was held on February 14–19, 2016 in Bandar Seri Begawan, Brunei.<ref>http://fta.mofcom.gov.cn/enarticle/rcepen/enrcepnews/201603/30820_1.html</ref>
*the 12th round of negotiation of RCEP was held on April 17–29, 2016in Perth, Australia. <ref>http://english.mofcom.gov.cn/article/newsrelease/significantnews/201605/20160501312566.shtml</ref>
*The 13th round of RCEP negotiation was held on June 12-18, 2016 in Auckland, New Zealand.<ref>{{cite web|title=Thirteenth Round of Negotiations for Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP) to be held in Auckland|url=https://www.mofa.go.jp/press/release/press4e_001174.html|website=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Japan|date=June 8, 2016}}</ref>
*The 14th round of RCEP negotiation was held on August 15–18, 2016 in Vietnam.
*The 15th round of RCEP negotiation was held on October 11–22, 2016 in Tianjin, China.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.mofcom.gov.cn/article/newsrelease/significantnews/201608/20160801383647.shtml|title=The 14th Round of Negotiation of Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership Held in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam -|author=|date=|website=english.mofcom.gov.cn}}</ref>
*The 16th round of negotiations of RCEP was held on  December 6–10 in Tangerang, Indonesia.
*The 17th round of negotiations of RCEP was held in Kobe, from February 27 to March 3, 2017 in Kobe, Japan.
*The 18th round of RCEP negotiation was held on May 8–12, 2017 in Manila, Philippines.<ref>http://www.dti.gov.ph/media/latest-news/10511-asean-fta-partners-meet-for-rcep-in-manila</ref>
*The 19th round of RCEP negotiation was held on July 24–28, 2017 in Hyderabad, India.<ref>{{cite web|last1=S|first1=Arun|title=India pressed to open up procurement|url=http://www.thehindu.com/business/india-pressed-to-open-up-procurement/article19366016.ece|website=The Hindu|language=en-IN|date=27 July 2017}}</ref>
*The 20th round of RCEP negotiation was held on October 17-28, 2017 in Incheon, Korea .<ref>{{cite web|title=20th Round of Negotiations for Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP)|url=https://www.mofa.go.jp/press/release/press4e_001754.html|website=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Japan|date=October 12, 2017}}</ref>
*The first RCEP summit was held on Nov 14.2017  in Manila, Philippines.<ref name="auto"/><ref>{{cite news|title=Now push RCEP, Abe-san|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/opinion/now-push-rcep-abe-san|work=The Straits Times|date=24 November 2017|language=en}}</ref>
*The 21st round of RCEP negotiation was held on February 2-9, 2018 in Yogyakarta, Indonesia.<ref>{{cite web|title=21st Round of Negotiations for Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP)|url=https://www.mofa.go.jp/press/release/press4e_001883.html|website=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Japan|date=January 29, 2018}}</ref>
*The 22nd round of RCEP negotiation was held from April 28 to May 8, 2018 in Singapore.<ref>{{cite web|title=22nd Round of Negotiations for Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP)|url=https://www.mofa.go.jp/press/release/press4e_002009.html|website=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Japan|date=April 25, 2018}}</ref>
*The 23rd round of RCEP negotiation was held on July 17-27, 2018 in Bangkok, Thailand.<ref>{{cite web|title=23th Round of Negotiations for Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP)|url=https://www.mofa.go.jp/press/release/press4e_002103.html|website=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Japan|date=July 12, 2018}}</ref>
*August-October 2018,  a series of ministerial meeting in Singapore and Auckland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/Politics/zW2jfnWbA20jrV3CTK0IBO/India-wins-key-concession-on-services-at-RCEP-Singapore-Mini.html|title=India wins key concession on services at RCEP Singapore Ministerial|author=Livemint|date=Sep 5, 2018|website=}}</ref> 
*The 24th round of RCEP negotiation was held on October 18-27, 2018 in Auckland, New Zealand.<ref>{{cite web|title=23th Round of Negotiations for Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP)|url=https://www.mofa.go.jp/press/release/press4e_002189.html|website=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Japan|date=October 16, 2018}}</ref>
*November 2018, Leaders' summit in Singapore where a broad agreement is expected.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/2162395/japans-relations-china-back-normal-track-says-shinzo-abe|title=US trade war and Japan push raise prospects for China-backed Asia free-trade deal|author=South China Morning Post|date=Sep 3, 2018|website=}}</ref>

== Controversies and criticism ==
{{Expand section|date=March 2017}}

RCEP has been criticized by [[free culture movement|free culture]] activists for containing "quite simply the worst provisions on copyright [...] ever seen in a trade agreement."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2016/04/rcep-other-closed-door-agreement-compromise-users-rights|title=RCEP: The Other Closed-Door Agreement to Compromise Users' Rights|date=2016-04-20|website=Electronic Frontier Foundation|access-date=2016-04-28}}</ref> Global health care activists have criticized the agreement for potentially forcing India to end its cheap supply of [[Generic drug|generic medications]] to poor countries.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2017/01/12/trumps-win-puts-tpp-in-danger-but-china-backed-trade-deal-may-not-gain-because-of-india.html|title=China-backed trade deal may not gain from TPP's loss. Blame India|last=Chandran|first=Nyshka|date=2017-01-12|website=CNBC}}</ref>

